## Contributing

### Commit Convention

All commits must follow the conventional commit format:

```
type(scope): description

Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore
Scopes: the affected module or area
Description: imperative lowercase, not past tense
```

### Branch Strategy

- Feature branches: `feat/*`, `fix/*`, `refactor/*`
- Never rebase -- only merge commits
- Force-push to feature branches is allowed
- Force-push to `main`/`master` is **blocked**

### Pull Request Checklist

Before submitting a PR:

- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Zero compiler warnings
- [ ] Code formatted (`cargo fmt`, `gofmt -w .`, `mix format`)
- [ ] Linter passes (`cargo clippy`, `go vet`, `mix credo`)
- [ ] Commit messages follow conventional commit format
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] All blocking operations have explicit timeouts
- [ ] All loops are bounded

